caption: Great service, great food! Chef Marcus talent really extends in the awesome unique recipes!
Nice ambiance, great service, good food & drinks @ affordable prices 👌.
Had a great time at red rooster over the weekend with my family and friends I will definitely be back to enjoy another delicious delight and bring a few friends with me for some drinks

LOVE this place! My first time here and it won’t be my last! My bartender Andres was perfect. His recommendations of the fritters and Mac & cheese were sooo good! His drink which was a floral gin drink he calls the Marie Clark Tayler (MCT) was amazing! I can’t believe it’s not on the menu! I love everything. I highly recommend it and I will be back.
Great food, great atmosphere, and great music. A must do when in Miami.
Great food with amazing atmosphere.  Can't wait to go back.
Very nice atmosphere, pleasant staff, but limited vegan options. There were two vegan options, a salad and charred cauliflower. We ordered both and they were tasty.
Had a wonderful meal, the service was spectacular! The Ambiance was very lovely friendly faces nice comfortable place to eat!
Great food, excellent and attentive service. The only drawback was the music was a bit loud, but we had an excellent time and will certainly be back!!
You must try the draft Sam Adam's very cold and goes down smooth.
Great vibe Great Food Good music Incredible Bar

First time at the restaurant and the food and the service was great. Chanel and the waiter from Somoa did a great job. Very kind and courteous. One thing though be careful with the sides in the  cast iron, the cast iron is very hot.  I burnt my finger on them. They brought me an ice pack to slow down the swelling and removed the hot cast iron  from the table. That's the only reason  for the 4 stars.
I had a great experience,Foods and drinks were amazing.. Love the live band on Sunday morning...I love the story of the place,Green Book.
First time dining at Red Rooster and the food was good.
What an experience!!! Food was amazing and atmosphere was top notch... The chicken and waffles (chefs kiss) and the mini donuts with guava... Mind blown!!! Worth the price and trip!!!

We had a reservation for 2:45 pm. When we arrive we were told to hurry up and place our order because the kitchen will be closing soon at the end of brunch. The other option was to come back after 4pm but we would have to reserve another table. This upsetting because this was never mentioned beforehand then someone told to not worry and take out time. This was a poor first impression, another con is that parking isn't free on the side parking of the building. We were there to celebrate my sister's birthday because we heard so much about the place and the owner. We ordered our waitress was incredibly nice and she was from historical Overtown (also where my father is from) she offered us a restaurant tour as well. The food was okay a bit pricey for such small portions. The cornbread was so delicious that we ordered 2. The deviled eggs were good but the caviar seemed unnecessary because you could not taste it. My family was not too impressed but I may return to try the creamery.
Great restaurant to dine in. Great food and service.
Simply incredible !!!! Food , music, service !!!
Great food, music and outdoor vibes

I love it here. My first night out, Marvin showed us around the building and there is wonderful art by black artists everywhere. Last night we didn’t have a reservation so I was nervous, but it wasn’t too busy of a night and the GM is super sweet and got me and my friend a table right away. Every time I come it seems to be an improved experience. Our waiter was very friendly and knowledgeable on the menu which is important. The bartender Chris is always super friendly and makes drinks based on our tastes. Definitely recommend for the vibes. The music/Djs are always really good. I recommend the chicken and waffles (vegan or non vegan, both are good), the blue crab spaghetti was great. I wish the chicken and waffles was on the dinner menu hehe. I personally enjoyed the cornbread, but can see how people may feel differently. I recommend to reserve if possible as it can get crowded later on in the day.
The drinks are very good and the decor is stunning. I was looking forward to my entree and apps, but the food was a bit pretentious and I was surprisingly disappointed.
I went here tonight for my 30th birthday and everything was amazing. The as staff was amazing and friendly. The food was sooooooooo good. We will be coming back very soon

Great food (chicken royale & collards amazing)!  And the oxtail.  Love the staff but the drink service/bar is poorly run.  I waited 20 minutes for my drink at the bar and the two times I sat down to eat my drinks were not delivered until mains after 30 minutes of appetizers.  I love the place and hope management fixes the bar service

Great place, I wasn't to sure about the menu, but once you tried it's amazing, the service was one of the best I ever had in a restaurant, and the decor and atmosphere was great, I would definitely be back.
One of the best dining experiences I've had. Outstanding service. Amazing vibe. Great food. Will definitely be back soon.
Great food even better service
(Translated by Google) Beautiful place .... excellent toilet  (Original) Hermoso lugar....excelente aseo

Wow! Run, don't walk - you must check this place out.  I went for an early dinner and had a reservation shortly after opening. By the time I left, the restaurant was popping with the most eclectic crowd! This is a super fun place to people watch. 🧐 Pictures can never do this restaurant justice.  You walk straight into an explosion of perfectly curated art, music memorabilia, architecture and decor that completely transports you to a happy place where you feel sexy, hip, cool and instantly hungry.  Well maybe the hungry part is because the aromas coming from the kitchen are absolutely divine! If you're an avid Top Chef watcher like myself you're already familiar with Chef Marcus Samuelsson.  His team includes GM Reggie Larose, Chef de Cuisine Tristen Epps and Director of Culture and Arts Donnamarie Baptiste and their highly trained and amazing staff.  Service is just right. I had Marcus' cornbread, the deviled eggs (please try!), an off the menu Heirloom salad, the Fried Yard bird and their tropical roots dessert, which is carrot cake with passion fruit, coconut, pineapple!! Trust me, my mouth is watering reminiscing about that meal.  Can you tell I'm in love?

The ambience was eclectic, the synergy, the vibe it just was breathtaking. I couldn't believe I was in Town like dat'. David our hosts was very professional, courteous, and as a black man that restaurant made me feel like I actually was home.

In the heart of the historic Overtown area of Miami, this restaurant was the birth of famed top chef Marcus Samuelsson🏆 Once you arrive you will feel like you’re transported to downtown Washington D.C.  at least that’s how I felt. Down to earth people with an artsy vibe. Live music on select nights. Make a rsvp because it gets busy here. Friendly staff, great food and the atmosphere is picturesque perfect 🤩
EVERYTHING we ordered was AMAZING! I will definitely go back.

The vibe in this place is GREAT, I can't argue that. The music, the casual buzzing around of people makes you feel like you've been transported somewhere else. The food is great but the flavors were turned down a bit to me to adopt to the wider palate. I'll definitely come back for the vibe and drinks tho. The music selection is awesome.
The food and atmosphere was great!! Make sure you book early for weekends dining.
Superb food, great drinks, cool music, good vibes and awesome service!!! One of my favorite restaurants!

First and foremost let me say that the atmosphere here is beautiful but the music was too loud. I ordered the chicken and waffles. The chicken was very salty, my first bite was disappointing. After sending it back I ordered the brisket which was to fatty and bland. I did not have a good experience here but that's just my opinion. Please visit and make your own opinion.
I will not be back to this restaurant for sure
Everything was excellent 👌
The place was awesome they had a bar and amazing food they had chicken macaroni and cheese and dessert mini cake with ice cream on top
The food is a little salty for my taste buds, but an overall vibe.  If you have high blood pressure, be careful.

Joann was very knowledgeable of the menu. Chef was kind enough to visit our table. The ox tail  was fall of the bone smokin!Soul food indeed. Beautiful art and delicious creamery...so many good things that I can not concrete in a small review.Overall a great experience, Thank you!

Service: staff was super friendly, very attentive about everything and they do go out their way to make sure you are comfortable. Amazing staff!!! Shout out to DJ the bartender  Ambience: it’s very loud, difficult to have a conversation, or communicate with the host or bartender. The decor is amazing, and the bar has very comfortable seating.  Parking: the restaurant offers self parking with a parking attendant who happens to be a manager with the worst customer service I have ever experienced. Flat out refused to give me a parking ticket when I asked for proof of payment, to a point where he threatened to tow my car just because I was asking for a parking ticket. The parking service definitely needs work.  The food: here is where my 1 star come from, I see other people reviews give the food high marks, but the food is unnaturally sour, my wife order the ribs which were so unnecessarily sour, I order the dark chicken which was highly under cook. It really tasted like honey chicken from a Chinese restaurant but just under cooked. For an appetizer we order the CCC fritters, which one was super over seasoned, and the other two had no seasoning. Eating the food was quite difficult, something I noticed is that nobody was able to finish the food. These reviews that I see people loving the food has me questioning if the other reviews about this place is true. The alcoholic drink are terrible. I believe the theme of this restaurant is citrus, everything has some sort of overwhelming amount of citrus in the drinks. Overall the food is terrible and the drinks are terrible. I posted picture of the items I would recommend you stay away from.  Overall: I believe this place can be something great but the menu needs to be re-evaluated. I alway give a place two visit. The first visit the food was horrible. I hope the second visit, the food does improves.
Awesome resturant! We went there for sunday brunch and it was memorable! Live music, delicious food, excellent service, nice place, charming ambiance. Definitely recommended!
Ambience 1-10 = 9 Service 1-10 = 10 Food 1-10 = 6  I need Tabasco with my oysters IJS!
Love this place! Ambience is amazing as well as the food. Live gospel music periodically is a nice touch.

Not only is the food something special the customer experience was phenomenal. My hubby and I had this spot on our list for a minute but then saw the owner and chef on GMA we had to get down there. Ryan greeted us with such a warm welcome. We waited in the veranda for our table but the ambience and drinks distracted us from what seemed like a very short wait. We were seated and was taken care of by Diana, an absolutely gem. Everyone we came in contact with was so kind and genuine. Now to the food. This was such a great experience and the food was superb.  We ordered the conch fritters for an appetizer, so good! Fried bird and Piccadilly spaghetti for our main courses. Everything was so fresh and tasty. The textures were lively and decadent. We ended it off with a specialty dessert, the hummingbird cake which I hope they add to their regular menu. Overall, a great experience with vibes and tasty plates.
The waiter Toni was amazing. The food was great and so good tasting. Everyone was so nice.

Everything was top notch:  venue, decor, vibe, service, food.  Just a great experience all around.  We had conch fritters, deviled eggs, bbq ribs, mac n cheese, shrimp n grits, and margaritas.  Conch was heavy on the red peppers, would pass next time but recommend all other dishes.
Couldn’t eat because the hostess never called a server to our table
The food was excellent. The service was impeccable. The vibe on a Monday was chilled. Music played well.
Great place! Outstanding service. Can't wait for their lunch menu.

Went for Brunch with my family. The atmosphere,music, service, and bar are top notch.  The food was okay in comparison. The french toast is for those with a sweet tooth, the signature beans bring a campfire feel to mind, the spicy avocado toast was fine. The Chicken and Waffles were the best of the bunch.

I almost don't want to write this review cause I wanna keep this place a secret and to myself but...  THIS PLACE IS AMAZING! The ambience, the food, the cocktails, the service (shoutout to Joanne!)...5 stars is not enough to do this Justice.  I decided to take a chance and skip the Chicken n' Waffles for the vegan version. Faux-Lafel Waffle - lentil waffle, "chicken-fried" maitake mushrooms, garlic whipped tofu, spiced syrup. I almost wanted to go vegan...but the bacon was too good to pass up.  Please come here, eat here, love here but most importantly...respect the work that has gone into celebrating the Black history that isn't told in Miamj.

Went to the new Red Rooster in Overton and had an amazing meal!! The food was incredible, and we ordered way more than we anticipated and it was WORTH IT!! We enjoyed a leisurely 3 hour dinner there on a week night and the staff was also very accomodating.  We asked to be sat next to an open window for safety/airflow and they did so.  When more ppl were sat near us and we felt it was too close, they happily moved us outside (it had rained earlier so they had to squeegee the patio) to accomodate us and make us feel more comfortable.  I believe our waiter’s name was Richard and b/w him and the host, they made our experience amazing!! Make sure you get there ASAP and ask for him!

This place is AWESOME!!! The ambience is amazing!! Food is too die for!! Topped off with GREAT SERVICE!!! Our table had the Whole Rooster, the Yardbird, and Spaghetti Picadilly.... add some mac and cheese, collard greens and corn bread.... AMAZING!!!

I don’t know what Patrick is talking about because this place deserves 5 STARS. The food + drinks was phenomenal when I went last night with my family. For our appetizers we ordered Deviled Eggs which were delicious & the corn bread - which I will admit was pretty dry. I don’t remember which cocktails we ordered but they were ALL so good and mixed very well. Then, for our entrees we ordered the Oxtail, Grilled Snapper, & the Fried Chicken with sides of Mac & Cheese, Collared Greens & the Jerk Sweet Potato.  Chile, listen. When I tell you the flavors of the food was hugging my taste buds?? I love it here, can’t wait to go back!  Shout out to Isaiah for recommending nearly everything. He has got great taste.
Isiah was one of the best servers I've ever had at a restaurant, and the food was incredible! Thank you all for such an amazing experience.  Would recommend to anyone!

3.40⭐️ Even though it was Friday night and the restaurant was packed, and we did not have a reservation, the hosts were super kind and friendly to find us a big table for six people. I almost went to the NYC location and heard great things about it, so I had big expectations. Being a comfort food restaurant, I was expecting that the cornbread will be mind-blowing, but it was super-average, so it started disappointingly. The fried chicken was the best thing there. It was amazing, really good! I wouldn’t serve the pigeon peas with it, and they were too hard. Mac & Cheese was also average, and the jerk sweet potato was great! The cocktail was a bit off — too sour, bitter, and boozy. Lastly, for my taste, the music was too loud, you could barely have a conversation. The ambiance and the atmosphere are beautiful. They did a good job. And all the staff is such kind, fast, and friendly people.
Absolutely A Great Vibe. Either on a date or with your friends. Service is A1. Don't judge by the neighborhood. It definitely needs to be on your bucket list...
Pricy but good
The BEST chicken I've ever had. The food was just good. There's nothing else to say. The service was great. The VIBE was everything. Just kiss the cook.

Was planning to do a Valentines takeout dinner featuring Red Rooster entrees for my family. I called both numbers all day Sunday from the website but got VM that were full (probably due to holiday demand). I decided i would order takeout in person only to learn from the hostess that takeout orders were not being allowed for Valentines Day. I would think that message should have been on the voice message for the restaurant as to alert patrons  that takeout order were not available.  I went to another local restaurant that did takeout order to save my Valentines family dinner. I know that Red Rooster is new to Miami,  but in this covid pandemic, it's better for my family to dine on take out at home than to dine-in only at your restaurantat this time.. We'll see you and dine-in when the coast is clearer.
Oxtail was out of this world! Thanks to Coco recommending it! Such a great spot :) must try!

We had the BEST experience at Red Rooster Overtown last night for Valentine’s Day! We are visiting Miami for the weekend and this place was recommend to us by a friend. We were amazed by all the food. The sea trout tiradito was to die for and I had the most amazing cocktail (the marqueta). The best part of our experience was our sever, Isiah. He was so knowledgeable, had amazing recommendations, and made us feel like family. 10/10 experience, highly recommend! Thanks Isiah :-)

Cool vibes with the dj. Nice atmosphere and cute decor.  Had an indoor outdoor seating.  The brunch food was very eclectic but not my taste. Had the smoked meat and potatoes with girl. The smoked pork was very vinegary not paired very well with the dish I dont think. Either way cool vibes would go back to try dinner
Great dining
Delicious food, great music... I ❤️  it there!!!!

Called to verify they were doing take out woman answers, and says yes absolutely just come to the bar to place your order. We drove 50 minutes only to be told no take out today no exceptions with a too bad attitude, even though their employee verified and I showed them my call log as proof of the call.  I’m sure the food is great, but you are nothing without customer service!

My man and I came for Sunday Brunch and we both had a great time! The ambiance was great and we both enjoyed our meals. The avocado toast (with bacon) and the Fried Yard Bird are two must trys. Our waitress Diana was absolutely amazing and a sweetheart! She went above and beyond our expectations and gave us wonderful service. We will be coming back and we will be requesting Diana as our server! if you're looking for good service, good food, and good vibes in Miami, Red Rooster is it.

Absolutely delicious! The restaurant is beautiful on the inside and the fried chicken is the best I've tried!  The blue crab pasta was also great, the mc & cheese is delightful as a side and the sweet potato is also really good!  Service is quick and attentive.  Overall an excellent experience! Highly recommend.

I made a reservation for 6:45 pm on our first night in Miami. The dress code at this establishment is casual as the hostess stated to me on the telephone it must be shoes, shirt, and pants. From the moment we walked in everyone was very welcoming and inviting. The entire establishment was ethereally beautiful! It oozed black pride with a modern retro vibe. From the music to the seating and wall decor, the place made you feel like you were in a dream! The waiter Isaiah was extremely attentive and upbeat. We ordered the share for two roasted chicken, macaroni and cheese, and greens which was amazingly delectable! They carmelize the chicken with an open flame and even cut the pieces up for you when they bring it out. I tried the lemonade, ginger beer, and tea which I didn’t find tasty. So Isaiah brought me a lemonade and didn’t charge me for the first drink. We also bought an overtown red rooster SnapBack for my boyfriend which was very nice and unique. I love that this establishment is black owned by Marcus Samuelson. He and his staff have done an amazing job with this restaurant and I hope it continues to thrive in the overtown community. We mentioned to the waiter that we’d love to have chef Marcus establish a location in Atlanta! Overall hands down I would recommend this location to anyone visiting Miami for the ambiance, beauty, and food!

A delightful experience on all levels from our Host, our Server Coco and the most Attentive and Hospitable Manager Freddy to the gorgeous cuisine. The Guayaba Donuts, the South Carolina Style  Smoked Meat, the Ceviche all accompanied by an exquisite pairing by Freddy of a Chianti ....all memorable. The ambiance is a celebration of life and the venue flows seamlessly from inside to outside in a way I have not seen executed so naturally. Bravo, Bravisimo
This was our first time here and I love it. The food,  service, ambiance and decor was amazing.  I will definitely be back!
The environment is electric, the drinks are great! And my must try is the guava filled donuts
Prices are too high...and food is not that good

Red Rooster is a fabulous restaurant that is located at 920 NW 2nd Avenue. The menu includes a potpourri of foods such as: Cornbread Loaf; deviled eggs; Chicken and Waffles; Foie Gras; Octopus; Fire Roasted Wagyu Oxtail; Grilled Yellowtail Snapper; Pound Cake; Mac and Cheese; Collard Greens; Red Endive Salad; Beef Ribs; Gambas Al Ajillo; Baked French Toast; and much more. For Black History Month (February) : week 1 - West & Central Africa; week 2 - The Caribbean; week 3 - New Orleans; week 4 - Low Country. Stop by and say hello to Chef Marcus Samuelsson and his team. The ambiance and decor of this restaurant will uplift you. Also, on site, is a food (semi) truck called Vice Burger. For the younger crowd, you will enjoy on the weekends half a block to the north The Urban - which plays contemporary hip hop as well as live acts. Tell them Jay sent you. Enjoy!.

The restaurant is alive. Loud contagious music playing and everyone enjoying the most interesting delicious food you ever tried. The service was excellent. The food beautiful and delicious. Can't wait to go back....

Interesting delicious food. Started off at the bar with cornbread and rum infused butter..west coast oysters.. Devil eggs.. We where just getting started. Had the whole fish that was prepared like no other fish .. So good.. With jerk sweet potato. Also crab rice came with the fish. Red Rooster servers and employees are so sweet and kind. We enjoyed the young staff ( most college kids as I ascertain). They where well trained and knew the menus. Valet was easy and felt completely safe in the historic district of Overtown. It was our pleasure to Eat Local and we are planning to take the ride again to check out the Sunday Brunch soon.
The decor and energy is amazing - it was like going back in time with a splash of amazing energy.
Fantastic food, service and ambience!!

The food and the place is absolutely amazing.. seriously recommend the fried chicken.. I think it is the best one I've had in my life.. great place to share plates, the only reason I'm giving this place a  stars it's because the tables are too small when you are seated with 4 pax.. if you are 4 pax or more I recommend you ask for a large table.
Food was amazing. Service was just as good.  Our server Joanne was on point and very friendly.  Would definitely go again.

I had an AH-mazing dinner at The Creamery at Red Rooster Overtown in Miami, FL (@roosterovertown)!  The original Red Rooster has been a staple in the heart of Harlem for years and although I never got to visit, I jumped when I heard that one recently opened in SOFLA! This location is a Southern/Caribbean/South American fusion!  Kudos to owner, chef, restaurateur and multiple james beard winner Marcus Samuelsson (@marcuscooks) for this beautifully designed spacious establishment located in the Overtown community.  Special shout to executive chef, winner of Food Network's Chopped and signature dish (Oxtails) mentioned on "The Best Thing I Ever Ate" Trini born Chef Tristan. @eppsandflows Those oxtails bruh!?!?!? Cooked with love!  This place is beautiful and has a different theme in every room.  They have an ice cream shop, two patios, bar, picnic area, multiple levels for private functions, african american history/art displayed all over the walls, etc. We had a wonderful server named Andre aka Dre who took care of us! He's very knowledgeable about food from around the world and gets excited about food such as myself! Great staff, customer service, music with a vibe, fun eye catching environment and delicious food!  **Marcus' Cornbread w/ Spiced RUM Butter** Review - Jiffy WHO? Perfection... warm and slathered with the smooth creamy spiced RUM butter! Moist, flavorful, slightly sweet and dense. I could eat all night.  **CCC Fritter ** Conch, corn, crab, collard green togarashi + green dipping sauce Review - It was good however the description made me think that I would taste all of these items in the fritter which I did not. It was a good fritter but nothing special.  **Not your Average Fancy Deviled Eggs** Topped with chicharron, caviar...mustard Review: I did not taste it however my friend and her significant other stated that it was very good.  I decided to have the Black History Month Special Menu... West and Central Africa cuisine  **Smoked African Giant Prawns** West African groundnut sauce, petite cabbage , crispy sweet potato Review - HUGE prawn with a nice smokey flavor and yummy crispy sweet potato topping.  **Suya Grilled Lamb** Suya Lamb (suya is a blend ground roasted peanuts, garlic and ginger powder, etc) with Jollof" broken ground grits, smoked charred onion, Get up sauce Review: The lamb was flavorful and cooked to perfection. Delish! The charred onions was an added bonus but wished the jollof broken ground grits had some flavor/bland.  **Malva Pudding** Red Rooster Style Review: Delicious! I can't tell you the amount of flavors this "pudding" had! The texture, unique flavors in every single bite, etc.  My friend chose the star of the show!!!!!!!!!!!!  **Fire Roasted Wagyu Oxtail** As seen on Food Network's 'The best thing I ever ate." Served whole, maduros, local bibb lettuce, truffle... Review: THE BEST OXTAILS I'VE EVERRR HAD!! Party in my mouth. This is the ENTIRE tail cooked to perfection...This is a 3 day process....Rubbed/Cured/braised in guava and red wine...star anise, sweet soy tamarind, chilis....black truffle and free herbs.....a side of the braising liquid, lemons, sea salt/smoked paprika to top...DELISH! The flavors were all over the place! This plate was for two. The three of us ate it and had to take it home. It looked like we hardly touched it b/c it was that big/meaty. Warning...$$$$ but worth it and its to sharte. We don't do this everyday! Enjoy!  **Mac and Cheese** Aged cheddar, chive, black pepper Review: It was creamy... gooey and had a nice crust/topping...If it was a little more sharp it would be top notch however it was very good!  Our male foodie had the ....  **Fried Yard Bird** Dark meat chicken, sour orange hot honey, baked pigeon peas, rooster hot sauce, pickles Review - This isn't your regular fried chicken. The chicken is brined in coconut milk, buttermilk and seasoned with an Ethiopian spice blend blessed with south orange hot honey.... The baked pigeon peas (my favorite type of peas) was a play on baked beans with a unique flavor. Foodiechews on IG
Great drinks, amazing atmosphere and ambiance!

Tried Red Rooster 2 weeks ago and was very impressed. Living in Miami with so many great dining options, it's hard to not have very high standards. We were extremely lucky to gave Isiah as our server.  We only ordered his recommended dishes and they were incredible. He was very knowledgeable about the entire menu, the owner & chef, as well as the history of the area and the building. The food was phenomenal- I highly recommend the Oxtail, the triple C fritters and the Bigeye Tuna Crudo.   We are coming back tonight for round 2!

I love Chef Samuelsson so I was very excited when my husband took me to this restaurant for my birthday.  I knew I had to have Marcus' Cornbread and it was amazing! The CCC Fritter were delicious.  My husband had the Grilled Yellowtail and he really enjoyed it.  I however ordered the Fried Yard Bird but my chicken was raw on the inside.  The food did take a while to come but it was a Saturday so I am assuming that's why.  Also, I would have liked more space between my table and the table next to me.  Other than that there are other things that I would like to try so I will definitely return.
I ordered the chicken and it wasn't cooked all the way but the cornbread was good. The music was amazing. Live band that made it worth the visit.
Excellent brunch, the music, the atmosphere, the service and most importantly, the food. The staff was so very attentive as well. I strongly recommend this restaurant.
Unbelievable, we sat at the bar for 15 minutes.  After we requested for menu.. the bartender slung the menu (unprofessional).  So disappointed had no choose but to walk out.
Friendly. Inviting, Great Food. Relaxing  Atmosphere.
Love the place food great and service is awesome.  Great music to
Awsome

Amazing! ‘Twas an exhilarating 1st experience... the ambience inviting, the food titillating (biscuit & gravy), and the service impeccable. I cannot wait to return. The Gospel Sunday Brunch is a must! Two thumbs up.👍🏾👍🏾
The service was wonderful everybody was nice and polite but the food wasn't that good and they're OVERPRICED!
We used to go to Red Rooster in Harlem all the time. It's great to have it in Miami. This Oxtail was amazing and the meat fell off the bone. A must try!
Fantastic.  Everything is excellent on the menu. Perfect limited list of fresh food, cooked to perfection!
Amazing venue, food was delish. Had cornbread, beet endive salad and fried chicken.  Each a unique version of the traditional dishes.
Very good place very nice and clean organized like the layout the food is good the price alright.
Food and service were amazing!! Definitely will be back.
Bisquit was delicious. I also had the chicken and waffles.  Staff is attentive and ensures your meal is to your expectations.
The atmosphere is amazing. The food is upscale soulfood.

This place was absolutely AMAZING!!!  The yellowtail snapper awakened tastebuds that I never experienced before.  So RIGHTEOUS!!!  I also attended the brunch yesterday, 1/17/2021.  Our waiter was absolutely amazing rather comical.  Just a suggestion regarding the gospel music—-Jazz would’ve been more accommodating to appease the diverse crowd.  Just a suggestion.  Other than that, I LOVE this place.
Waste of Time

Went on a Sunday night and it was packed. Very classy spot! One of the owners gave us a mini tour and made great recommendations. The live band was everything. To drink we chose the Marqueta and the Maison 920. The entrées are a la carte. We had the Grilled Yellowtail Snapper and the Sour Orange Pig Ribs. For sides we shared the Mac & Cheese and the Succotash. It was all delightful and yummy. Their menu is very different from the norm. It's black owned and operated, it shows a nice piece of Miami history.
Great service, tasty drinks and the food was well executed
Nice spot that they had the lil trap house Miami cool job to t.i bring it back to Miami
great for happy hour! $5 apps $2 oysters $8 cocktails. live the decor, the music and the vibe

Red Rooster is what I like to call a “limited edition” restaurant. The space itself oozes personality and the location has great provenance or history. But most importantly, the team (especially my waiter, Brandon) does all the little things that make you feel special.  Limited edition restaurants are rare but when they work the demand FAR outweighs supply. So make your reservations in advance.  Before leaving I booked dinner for my best friend’s birthday next week. As if we needed an excuse to get the famous oxtail (only 10 available per night LOL - very limited edition). Go Red Rooster go!
The food, people and music was amazing...Oh and thee best waitress ever,  Diana aimed to please and was a treat to have as our Waitress!

Great experience. As others have noted the decor was beautiful. Whoever designed the restaurant really earned their money. The food  was also fantastic and well worth what you pay for it. We had the scallops with the mushroom ponzu sauce, the deviled eggs with the chicharrón, and the cornbread. All delicious.  For the main I went with the Yardbird with an extra side of Mac and Cheese ( Do NOT substitute the beans with the Mac And Cheese. Get them both. Those beans that come with the bird have a touch of sweetness that goes really well with the brininess of the bird. The Chef made it that way for a reason so don't mess with it ! ) Get the mac dude, treat yourself, it's just 9 bones and you can share it.  My girl had the Picadilly pasta which was great.  Our server Brandon was fantastic. His charm was natural and effortless while his hospitality was focused and thorough. His service was impeccable but it was his hospitality that really shone through the service. He made us feel welcome and he exuded a genuine interest in how our meal was going every step of the way. Truly an asset to this restaurant.  This restaurant is a definite recommend and if you have an opportunity to ask for Brandon I really recommend it.

Yesterday I concluded my birthday celebration at Red Rooster. The location has significant sentimental value for me because I am from Historical Overtown.  Mavin warmly greeted us at the door and promptly seated us. His hospitality alone sold me almost immediately and he went above and beyond to ensure I had a great birthday. The venue was otherworldly, drinks were exemplary and the service was incredible. Thank you Marvin, Marcelo and Stevens for helping to create the best birthday Ive ever had... in my home! I look forward to sharing more memories at Red Rooster!

The restaurant has a nice ambiance. I love it is in a historical area. The food was good and our server was very attentive. It is very spacious. Marcus and Marvin made sure everything was going well with our dining experience. Educated us on the art that was displayed in the restaurant. Will definitely come back and I have already referred others to try it out. The cornbread ❤️
Great atmosphere. Delicious flavorful food. Outstanding service. The only complaint I have are the small portions for the appetizers and the entree. The dessert made up for it though. 🤤

I've been a fan of Red Rooster since going to the Harlem location in New York. I love the history of the town with the vintage archive photos. So I've been anticipating going to the Red Rooster in Overtown. I went back in December and fell completely in love with the entire experience. I came back for the gospel brunch. I was in food heaven. The weather was great. The band was amazing. And the food was exactly what I imagined and more. I strongly recommend the homemade lemonade! I ordered deviled eggs the cornbread, The chicken and waffle (it had a kick!) And the french toast.  Parking is valet or there's easy street parking right in front of you if you go early. There's so much more happening at Rooster that I can't wait to become a regular. Bonus: There's a cute ice cream shop called the Creamery adjacent to it that's incredible!

My very first time coming to the Red Rooster Overtown first things first I want to thank them it was my birthday and I love the atmosphere it was a very cool Vibe the food was excellent The Wailers was very knowledgeable about the food the shelves came and explained what the dishes was about and what expired the dish all around it was amazing I will love to go back there again and I recommend everybody else to do the same

I had reservations and waited an hr to be told that the people at our table "are not moving." The hostess suggested we eat at the lounge area. We asked to sit at another table, and she said that it was reserved for larger parties than for us 2. So, you guys would rather us wait another hr than give us a table that's been empty for 20 min? So ridiculous. We are so disappointed that we wasted our time and I highly anticipated date night on this foolishness. I'm simply writing to let you know how useless making reservations is at your restaurant. I won't be recommending Red Rooster to anyone and will most likely not to ever try stopping by again.
First day of open brunch, ambience was amazing. Disc jockey on point great music selection.  Server Wesley was phenomenal,  very patient and friendly with our party!! Amazing restaurant

Red Rooster rocks !!!! I was fortunate enough to spend my NYE dinner at red rooster, service was impeccable !!!! Isaiah was the best !!!! Will definitely be a frequent flyer at this location THE FOOD, THE AMBIANCE & THE DRINKS !!!! A MUST TRY !!!!
Literally everything was delicious. I loved the greens. I could eat them as a main dish! The octopus was mouth-watering. CCC fritters...wow!!

Miami rarely impresses me but Red Rooster left me speechless. From the extensive well thought out menu, the amazing staff, attentive server ( Wesly!), and the extraordinary decor - Red Rooster is here to stay. The music and lighting is a  vibe

About a week ago I visited for the first time with my siblings and I can say the good things I heard were true! The food was amazing and the environment made us feel right at home including decor related to the African American experience. Our server's name was Isaiah but he had us call him Ike. His smile was so bright and he encouraged me to try the Fried Yard Bird which was phenomenal! He made us feel like we had known him for years. The Marcus' cornbread was great as well!
I don’t even know where to begin! This place is phenomenal. From the flawless service to the delicious food, it is an amazing dining experience! We will definitely be back!

Great experience! Happy that the night I went the  Chef was there over seeing things. The restaurant has a very nice decor, and atmosphere. Wesley was amazing very knowledgeable on the menu and made sure we had everything we needed. We had the corn bread, tiradito, fried chicken,and the oxtail. All plates were amazing drinks heavy. This was my birthday I had a great time. I will be back

Amazing staff! They were all so attentive and helpful!  Ambience was majestically beautiful!  Food was delicious! We dined on Oxtails, Collards, Mac and Cheese, Cornbread, Seafood Tower, Spaghetti Piccadilly, Fried Yard Bird, Strawberry Lemonade, Gladys Knight & The Sips, Tito’s & Pineapple, and The Brownstone. Nothing disappointed us at all!

The food is immaculate! I went there last night and our server Wesley had to be the icing on the cake! He was so well versed about things on the menu and he had the patience of a saint. His recommendations did not disappoint. We even ordered desert and we're able to finish eating it with no issue (they began cleaning up to close). Wesley did not put the bill on the table until he knew and assured we were done with our experience! There’s nothing better than great food, than great customer service. I will be back.

This place is an experience. Period. My server Wesley brought me the biggest plate of ox tail in existence. They have different flavors for every soulfood dish you can think of. You can tell the chef is a true artist an has an extensive palette. Their presentation is amazing an the ambience is great. An incredibly well styled restaurant that truly has a vibe like no other in Miami. Everything here was phenomenal.... tehe only asterisk here truly for me were the drinks. Although fresh an creative they were the least impressive things on the menu. Still my company enjoyed thier drinks so Im not taking a star off for this slight asterisk. Im stuck between highly recommending this place & recommending it to the squad. If you are debating this place stop debating & go asap before there is 1 hour waits to get a reservation here.

I was a regular at Red Rooster Harlem, so my expectations and enthusiasm for Overtown were high. The service was excellent. Everything else was not. The rubbery and waxy deviled eggs tasted as if they were made in advance and refrigerated for hours. (We were brought a new order which tasted exactly the same.) The ribs, greens, and steak were nice, although the potatoes that joined the steak were room temperature. The real issue, and the reason I can’t imagine ever returning: the noise. The music was so intolerably loud, it ruined the experience. I love a good party, but not when I’m at what should be an excellent restaurant and the music distracts from the food. And, to top it off, the mixing of the songs was so disjointed and inorganic that it was offensive. The restaurant is stunning. The service, as I said, is lovely. Why ruin the experience with music so loud you can’t even have a conversation? I left the restaurant feeling bummed that my experience wasn’t better than it should’ve been. Keeping a restaurant open, especially these days, must be extraordinarily challenging. So it’s surprising and disappointing that some really simple adjustments could have made this a much better, more inviting experience. I really hope things improve.

Wow! This restaurant was absolutely amazing. The food was incredible, especially the spaghetti Piccadilly  and the Mac and cheese! The desserts are also great. Our server, Elijah, was super friendly and attending. The ambiance was perfect, and the live dj made the night even more fun. Would 10/10 recommend!!
The waiter Wesley provided amazing service. I will definitely come again. Great atmosphere and delicious food.

This place was amazing nice to see an upscaled mixed crowed, had a real classic NYC vibe. Had the OX tail and mannnn was it good, and all of the sides are great I had 3 of them ( Mac, greens, and sweet potato) the place had a DJ also great. So it was a 1 stop shop for me and my date, dinner, drinks and music
Excellent service...great food... nice ambiance.

Omg.... It was absolutely Melt in Your Mouth Delicious.  CONGRATULATIONS on a very Successful the Opening. The Staff was amazing and So accommodating. I had a wonderful Birthday Dinner. I ordered the Fire Roasted Wagyu Oxtail the Cornbread with bourbon butter and the CCC Fritters. I will Be Back For sure!😋

Amazing food, ambiance, and style.  This place is so clean and the service is really friendly.  Great place to hang out!  Parking is safe and it is close to downtown and Brickell.  The vibe is amazing!

First I must say our waitress INDIA was super. Great customer service ,very pleasant. Ok now the food from the appetiser to the drink and entrees was not so good not much flavour  .. I had the flitter and the corn bread , and ribs   None was my favourite..my friend had the same expect her entree was the spaghetti wasn’t tasteful.I gave a three star because our waitress was great .. if I could give her all five I would but then I wouldn’t be able to grade the food..

Our experience here yesterday with sever Wesley was amazing he was very knowledgeable , friendly, and entertaining .  The food was great he gave us good recommendations such as the fritter and  the griot  and the famous Fried chicken .We will be back  And request for him.
I recently visited Red Rooster. The food was absolutely amazing. The service was so kind and welcoming. I will for sure be back again. Order the Mac & Cheese!
Amazing food, great atmosphere, easy parking and perfect service (Wesly was awesome!)
The aesthetic is next level. The food was out of this world. And the service was unparalleled. WESLEY was the best - super friendly, helpful, and kept us laughing. Will definitely be going back asap!
Shrimp and grits are the best I've had, the fried chicken, mac n cheese and the snapper were 🔥🔥🔥 too

@yay.tamera- Okay let’s talk about @roosterovertown ‼️ I had the pleasure of attending their soft opening this week where I tried their deviled eggs appetizer, Grilled Yellowtail Snapper, and Fried Yardbird. I loved the coconut addition to the snapper and enjoyed dinner.  However, I returned for dinner last night and was blown away! Everything was absolutely amazing. Our table side presentation for the Smoked Rooster Royale was a tantalizing experience. The sides also included were so flavorful and filling. We ended the night perfectly with the Sundae #AF dessert 🍨  Throughout the night we enjoyed a specially crafted @bacardiusa cocktail the bartender Nick named the “Sweet Sensation.” ❤️  Red Rooster hands down is now on my top 5 dinner spots list* #blackrestaurantweek
The food is amazing and cocktails. You will fall in love with🔥 Red Rooster Restaurant 🔥

Vibe✔✔✔ Food ✔✔✔ Music ✔✔✔  Listen, this is an experience.  Everything was great. The DJ was on point with the neo soul. Our waiter Wesley was on point with all of his suggestions. Like the only thing missing was my photo op with Marcus himself. Thanks to my husband for finding this gem for date night.

I would like to take the time out of my busy day of being the creative Chef that I am and let all of you who are writing bad reviews to not judge your first experience and judge your second time. This food establishment is one of those unique restaurants to hit Miami and for it to be in the heart of Overtown is speaking volumes. Red Rooster has a collection of individuals working there to bring you an entertaining and welcoming experience. The food is on another level. Those who experienced poor food or raw chicken I am really sorry you experienced that because "baby" their food is off the chain. Maybe they rushed to open during the pandemic to please you people when they should of just stayed closed. Marvin Roger's one of the top managers any establishment would want for their business. Y'all better be good by Mr. ROGER'S, people are dying to hire him.. lol, I am one of them. Last but not least the Chef thst holds it down Tristien Epps. Big personality, and one of the secret ingredients to Red Rooster Overtown.
They are closed permanently according to their voicemail. The store had a closed sign on it as well.
Marcus doesn’t disappoint. Quality bird, great prices, and ice cream for dessert.

I’ve visited twice already and I’ve enjoyed both visits. First time I had the crispy bird dog and it was good. Service was excellent. Went again and invited my parents for lunch.  We ordered the Family Supper and it fed our group of 4 and we took leftovers home as well. The platter brings 8 pcs of chicken (fried yardbird & rooster royale), mac & cheese, baked beans, and collard greens as sides. In addition, an appetizer (we had smoked fish dip) and dessert (creamy sundae cup). Food was fantastic. Chicken was juicy and sides were some of the best I’ve had in some time, particularly the greens.  What I enjoy most about this spot is how attentive and welcoming their staff is. First class all the way thru. I highly recommend everyone to try this spot.
Delicious. I had the chicken and waffles with the Mac n cheese. Also the red velvet and cornbread cream. It was so good. I'm going to take a nap now.

AMAZING AMERICAN CUISINE with a delicious island flare to it! Absolutely refreshing! The prices are PERFECT & the amount of food is generous per serving. We ate what we could & took the rest Home. EXCELLENT Customer Service! Love how everyone kept checking in on Us. Even the Boss was engaging with the Customers. Social Distancing Guidelines were observed & even a Sanitizing Station was set up outside. BRAVO GUYS! This is a prime example of how an eatery should conduct Business in a Pandemic situation. Thanks for the really awesome eats! Can't wait to come back!

Cant wait for them to open up. Once all these crazy floridians calm down and wear masks so we can get covid under control. (Notice Republican run states with all the covid cases?) Either way. Ice cream was excellent. Made a suggestion that they have empty containers for us to choose our own take home ice cream. That guava ice cream is amazing. Same for the corn bread. Chicken mac and cheeses is excellent. Greens a lil too sweet for me. I'll be going back often.
Amazing food!!! Perfect amount of food. Definitely ordering again

On June 27, 2020 we went to this restaurant full of expectations for two reasons. A) having been in Samuelson's Harlem restaurant and b) having been in the original red rooster that was a cornerstone of Harlem. Sadly, to say this experience was poor. The staff were excellent, pleasant and made sure you were happy and satisfied. However, what came out of the kitchen was no so. One order was chicken in waffles. The thigh was huge which created a cooking problem, the inside was raw. The pickled cabbage should be renamed the spicy cabbage and the syrup for the waffles was also too spicy. The other odor was Fried Yardbird. Again, the leg was huge and center raw. We need not cut the other piece of chicken.  Sorry but this  gets no raves for food but the staff were great.

The Creamery ... the  best fried chicken that I’ve had from any restaurant in South Florida . Perfectly cooked , well seasoned batter .. great crunch .  Flavorful collards on the side .. I can’t wait for the Red Rooster to open to try the rest of the menu !

I want to first start off by saying the service was amazing. My family and I were greeted as if we were their own family. Now on to the food! Holy smokes the fried chicken and waffles was one of the best I’ve had in Miami. The skin was crispy and flavorful and the inside was juicy and delicious. We also got the crispy bird dog which was equally amazing! My kids loved the Vanilla ice cream. It is safe to say we will definitely be back!!

I ordered take out today for my kids and I. And, I must say.. well first off, we were greeted by a handsone gentleman by the name of Isaiah.  Very confident and great energy. I immediately felt welcomed. Ok now the food. I ordered the "Rooster Royale Creamery Style." Omg .. everything was on point! No.. seriously!! My most favorite was the GREENS. Like omg.. I'm not huge on veggies at all, but I sure did scrape the bowl. You all definitely "put your foot in it." like the old folks would say back in the day, when the food was on point. I highly recommend. Thank you for blessing the neighborhood and WELCOME.

So excited they opened this weekend! Amazing. Clean, delicious, welcoming, it was perfect. We ordered takeout before arriving and wanted to order ice cream while we waited and the food was ready quickly, the line was controlled impeccably during the COVID situation, and we just felt so comfortable stepping in. Not to mention everything we tried was delicious!
Really am looking forward to trying this place out!!!
All in!!  Can’t wait. 🙏🏻

Grove Bay Hospitality Group is one of the BEST restaurants groups located here in the heart of Miami! The atmosphere is always amazing, along side their outstanding dishes. I really am looking forward to trying this place out!
Looking forward to eat here
